<DocsLayout title="Getting Started">
<div class="prose">

<h1>Getting Started</h1>

<p>Get Qwenta deployed on your VPS in under 10 minutes.</p>

<h2>Prerequisites</h2>

<ul>
  <li>A VPS (Ubuntu 22+ recommended) with at least 4GB RAM</li>
  <li>Node.js 18+</li>
  <li>PostgreSQL 14+</li>
  <li>Ollama installed on the VPS</li>
  <li>A domain name (optional but recommended for SSL)</li>
</ul>

<h2>1. Clone &amp; Install</h2>

<p>SSH into your VPS and run:</p>

<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/your-org/qwenta
cd qwenta
npm install</code></pre>

<h2>2. Configure Environment</h2>

<pre><code>cp .env.example .env</code></pre>

<p>Edit <code>.env</code> with your VPS settings:</p>

<pre><code>DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@127.0.0.1:5432/qwenta
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen2.5
SESSION_SECRET=generate-with-openssl-rand-hex-32
PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://your-domain.com</code></pre>

<h2>3. Setup Database</h2>

<pre><code># Create database
createdb qwenta

# Run migrations
node scripts/migrate.js</code></pre>

<h2>4. Setup Ollama &amp; Qwen</h2>

<pre><code># Install Ollama on your VPS
curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh

# Pull Qwen model
ollama pull qwen2.5

# Verify it's running
curl http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags</code></pre>

<h2>5. Build &amp; Run</h2>

<pre><code># Build for production
npm run build

# Start the server
npm start
# Runs on port 4321</code></pre>

<h2>6. Reverse Proxy (Nginx)</h2>

<p>Set up Nginx to proxy requests to Qwenta with SSL:</p>

<pre><code>server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name your-domain.com;

    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/your-domain.com/fullchain.pem;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/your-domain.com/privkey.pem;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:4321;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}</code></pre>

<h2>7. Connect Your Wallet</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open <code>https://your-domain.com</code></li>
  <li>Click <strong>Connect Wallet</strong></li>
  <li>Select MetaMask, Phantom, or any WalletConnect wallet</li>
  <li>Sign the SIWE message (no transaction)</li>
  <li>You're in the dashboard</li>
</ol>

<h2>Deploying with Docker</h2>

<pre><code>FROM node:20-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install
COPY . .
RUN npm run build
EXPOSE 4321
CMD ["npm", "start"]</code></pre>

<pre><code># With Docker Compose
docker-compose up -d</code></pre>

<h2>Process Management (PM2)</h2>

<p>Use PM2 to keep Qwenta running on your VPS:</p>

<pre><code># Install PM2
npm install -g pm2

# Start Qwenta
pm2 start npm --name "qwenta" -- start

# Auto-restart on reboot
pm2 startup
pm2 save</code></pre>

<h2>Environment Variables Reference</h2>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Variable</th><th>Required</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>DATABASE_URL</code></td><td>Yes</td><td>—</td><td>PostgreSQL connection string</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>OLLAMA_BASE_URL</code></td><td>—</td><td><code>http://127.0.0.1:11434</code></td><td>Ollama server URL on VPS</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>OLLAMA_MODEL</code></td><td>—</td><td><code>qwen2.5</code></td><td>Model name</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>SESSION_SECRET</code></td><td>Yes</td><td>—</td><td>Min 32 chars for session signing</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>PUBLIC_APP_URL</code></td><td>—</td><td><code>https://your-domain.com</code></td><td>Public URL for SIWE domain</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

